      <h2>Taxicard</h2>

<p>This is a subsidised scheme&nbsp;for people using taxis and minicabs. Taxicard provides transport for London residents with mobility impairments or who are sight impaired.</p>

<p><a href="/modes/taxis-and-minicabs/taxicard-and-capital-call">Find out about Taxicard</a>.</p>

<h2>Community Transport</h2>

<p>Community Transport can also provide door-to-door transport to people in local communities who can't use mainstream public transport, allowing them to access work, training and social activities.</p>

<p><a href="/transport-accessibility/community-transport">Find out about Community Transport</a>.</p>

<h2>Dial-a-Ride</h2>

<p>Dial-a-Ride is our door-to-door service. It's free for people who are unable to use&nbsp;public transport. Dial-a-Ride can be used for trips such as shopping, visiting family and travelling to leisure activities.</p>

<p><a href="/modes/dial-a-ride/index">Find out about Dial-a-Ride</a>.</p>
      
           
      
      
        
          
